Selecting a Mask: Do‚Äôs & Don‚Äôts

CDC
August 28 at 8:52 AM ¬∑

Wear a mask when you‚Äôre in public to help slow the spread of COVID-19. When selecting a mask, you have many choices. Avoid masks that are made of materials that make it too hard to breathe. Also avoid masks with valves or vents that allow virus particles to escape and masks that should be saved for healthcare workers. Wear cloth masks with two or more layers to help protect yourself and others from COVID-19.

Learn more about the do‚Äôs and don‚Äôts of masking: https://bit.ly/30QOzQF.

Iowa Department of Public Health
August 21 at 8:06 AM ¬∑

Additional food replacement assistance is now available for Iowa WIC families. Families currently receiving benefits and living in Benton, Boone, Cedar, Clinton, Dallas, Jasper, Johnson, Jones, Linn, Marshall, Muscatine, Polk, Poweshiek, Scott, Story and Tama counties can request to replace WIC foods that were purchased between August 1-10 and were damaged by the August 10 derecho.

WIC families must contact their local WIC agency no later than August 31 to request food replacement. https://bit.ly/34rkZot

Visit https://idph.iowa.gov/WIC for more information on WIC and to find your local agency.

shared_text:
Riverside Title One Program
August 17 at 1:00 PM ¬∑

Hello Families!

Hope everyone had a great summer. Looking forward to a great school year and to be back in the classroom together again. A couple of changes as this year gets underway. No Title 1 Family Meeting this year. However, we are always available to answer questions and talk with you. Please feel free to call or email either one of us with any questions or concerns throughout the year. We are in the process of scheduling students for the upcoming year and are going to do everything we can to meet all students needs and to help them thrive as readers. Please keep watching this page for updates and happenings throughout the year. Go Bulldogs!

Thanks,
Ms. Vollmar: K-2 Grade Title 1 Instructor
Mr. Blair: 3-5 Title 1 Instructor

No Title 1 Family Meeting this year. However, we are always available to answer questions and talk with you. Please feel free to call or email either one of us with any questions or concerns throughout the year. We are in the process of scheduling students for the upcoming year and are going to do everything we can to meet all students needs and to help them thrive as readers. Please keep watching this page for updates and happenings throughout the year. Go Bulldogs!

Thanks,
Ms. Vollmar: K-2 Grade Title 1 Instructor
Mr. Blair: 3-5 Title 1 Instructor

shared_text:
Nishna Heritage Museum of Oakland, Iowa
August 4 at 10:52 AM ¬∑

After putting out an appeal for donations to help us repair the Heft part of the museum, Ruth and Jeep Miller and Greg Robinson sent us checks. We have received pledges from Clark Christensen, Nikki Allen Osborn, Tom King, Susan Baker, Doug Finnegan, Tami Scofield, and Kris Pierce. Although most no longer live in Oakland, we are pleased they still feel connected to their high school and community. We feel blessed to have known these people as they sat in our classrooms and that they care to give back. Thank you so much. If anyone else would like to donate, we would be so grateful.
text:
Nishna Heritage Museum of Oakland, Iowa
August 4 at 10:52 AM ¬∑

After putting out an appeal for donations to help us repair the Heft part of the museum, Ruth and Jeep Miller and Greg Robinson sent us checks. We have received pledges from Clark Christensen, Nikki Allen Osborn, Tom King, Susan Baker, Doug Finnegan, Tami Scofield, and Kris Pierce. Although most no longer live in Oakland, we are pleased they still feel connected to their high school and community. We feel blessed to have known these people as they sat in our classrooms and that they care to give back. Thank you so much. If anyone else would like to donate, we would be so grateful.

July 6 at 4:56 PM ¬∑

DHS announced the distribution plan for $76,268,223 in Food Assistance benefits for Iowa Families who lost access to free or reduced price meals due to school closures. Families will begin receiving benefits on July 14.

For families already receiving food assistance, the benefits will be added to their current EBT cards. For non-food assistance families, the cards will arrive in the mail July 14-21, 2020.

For full details on who will receive the benefits and how to access them, please visit our website: https://dhs.iowa.gov/P-EBT

Leslie Waddell Amdor shared a post to the group: Riverside After Prom.
June 22 at 4:55 AM ¬∑

Leslie Waddell Amdor is with Jamie Goodman and 81 others.
June 9 at 5:25 AM ¬∑

Parents sponsored Prom

The Riverside Senior parents are having a Senior/Junior Prom night, Saturday, July 18th. It will take place at the Carson Community Building and students can start arriving at 8:15-8:30pm for pictures and will run until midnight.

We will provide more details and any changes made after signup and we will follow CDC guidelines as well. In order for this event to happen, we will need parent volunteers for the evening with set up, take down, dance chaperones, and providing snacks/drinks and decorations. Please email killianredm@msn.com with any questions that you might have.

Students please sign up by emailing Kelly Edic (killianredm@msn.com) no later than, June 30th, 2020.

post_text:
Riverside Students & Families!!

If you have already turned in your child's Chromebook you do not need to worry about this post.

We would like to extend an offer to our Bulldog Families to use the school Chromebooks over the summer of 2020. In order for this to happen we will need for you to acknowledge that you have the Chromebooks and verify that you understand that you are responsible for any damage or loss of the Chromebook or its parts. Please check your email for access to the form to submit student names, family contact information and select that you understand about damages and loss.

We will be having a drop off night in Carson on Wednesday, May 27, 4:00 p.m. - 6:00 p.m. where you can drop off any library books and Chromebooks. We are looking at other nights and locations for drop off other than food distribution so stay tuned.

Any Chromebooks not returned by Monday, June 1 or have not submitted the form to keep the Chromebook, will be locked and become unusable.

Any questions can be directed to Mr. Meek, jmeek@riverside.k12.ia.us.

post_text:
Riverside-Returning of School-Owned Computers

We are planning on providing Voluntary Educational Enrichment Opportunities until the end of the school year, which is May 22, 2020. That is our official last day of school.

So, if you need to keep your child's school computer until that time, we will facilitate a computer return after the end of the school year.

If your child brought home the school computer and it has sat around and not been used or your child has decided to use another computer that you have at home, please return the school computer when you come to pick up your personal belongings. That way you don't have to worry about it getting lost or broken.

Again, we are planning on providing Voluntary Educational Enrichment Opportunities until May 22 so if you need the computer to keep participating, please keep it and look for our next announcement for computer turn in.

Tim Mitchell
April 29 at 11:05 AM ¬∑

Riverside Community School District

Will we be offering Driver Education this Summer?

Yes--the district will offer Driver Education this Summer-we are waiting for final guidance from the Iowa Department of Transportation and Iowa Department of Education. We are told that this joint guidance will be distributed soon.

Will we have Prom, Spring Sports, Club Activities, or Summer Sports?

Due to the extended closure, the earliest we would start sports or other activities would be June 10, 2020. Spring sports have been cancelled by the Athletic Associations for this year. We will not schedule any summer sports, summer workouts/practices, activities until we have guidance that indicates we can resume these activities safely.

Prom has been tentatively scheduled for Saturday June 27, 2020.

shared_text:
Tim Mitchell
April 29 at 10:30 AM ¬∑

Riverside Community School District
When will the school year end?
Even though learning has looked different over the last four weeks, opportunities have still been provided for students. Because of this, the State of Iowa has approved or forgiven these days, and the days moving forward.

We will plan on ending the school year on the regularly scheduled dismissal date of May 22, 2020. Our focus will then switch to planning for our students' return. We know that a lot of work needs to be done next year to help our students meet grade level standards and we want to be as prepared as possible.

post_text:
Riverside--Parents and Guardians of the class of 2020!

Please access the link provide to complete a survey for options for graduation for the class of 2020. Please take the time to discuss this survey with your senior, and jointly complete the survey by Wednesday, April 29, 2020.

The original plan that the seniors came up with was a hybrid graduation on May 17 at 2:00 pm. For this option, graduates/family (Graduate plus 2 parents/guardians) would drive up to the school and be ushered into the school and across the stage per Governor Reynolds social distancing guidelines. The ceremony would be broadcast live on Facebook and the radio. We would also record the graduation for a video at a later date. Thank you for completing this survey. We will compile data, and make a graduation decision by May 4, 2020.

#weRriverside



Graduation Survey Link: https://forms.gle/6dN9dJ6W1murtjPKA
